params.quantityQuoteTokens: The quantity of quoteTokens to add with optionTokens to the Uniswap V2 Pair.
params.to: The address that receives UNI-V2 shares.

deployUniswapMarket(address).details: Creats a Uniswap pair for option<>quote tokens.

params.optionAddress: The address of the option to deploy a Uniswap V2 Pair for with the quoteToken.

flashloanMintShortOptionsThenSwap(addres.details: Mints long and short option tokens using a flash loan from UniswapV2. Then sells short tokens, and pays the difference.

params.amountOutMin: The minimum quantity of underlyingTokens to receive in exchange for the redeemTokens.
params.deadline: The timestamp for a trade to fail at if not successful.
params.flashLoanQuantity: The quantity of options to mint.
params.optionToken: The address of the Option contract.
params.path: The token addresses to trade through using their Uniswap V2 pools. Assumes path[0] = redeemToken.
params.to: The address to send the redeemToken proceeds and optionTokens to.

returns._0: bool Whether the transaction was successful or not.

getMaxDeadline().details: The maxmium deadline available for each trade.

getUniswapMarketForOption(address).details: Gets a Uniswap Pair address for an option token and quote token.

params.optionAddress: The address of the option to get a Uniswap V2 Pair address for (with quoteToken).

getUniswapMarketForSeries(address,addres.details: Gets a Uniswap Pair address for the corresponding option parameters.

mintOptionsThenSwapToTokens(address,uint.details: Mints options using underlyingTokens provided by user, then swaps on Uniswap V2. Combines Primitive "mintOptions" function with Uniswap V2 Router "swapExactTokensForTokens" function.

params.amountIn: The quantity of options to mint and then sell.
params.amountOutMin: The minimum quantity of tokens to receive in exchange for the optionTokens.
params.deadline: The timestamp for a trade to fail at if not successful.
params.optionToken: The address of the Oracle-less Primitive option.
params.path: The token addresses to trade through using their Uniswap V2 pools. Assumes path[0] = option.
params.to: The address to send the optionToken proceeds and redeem tokens to.

returns._0: bool Whether the transaction was successful or not.

mintShortOptionsThenSwapToTokens(address.details: Mints long and short option tokens, then swaps the shortTokens (redeemTokens) for tokens.

params.amountIn: The quantity of options to mint.
params.amountOutMin: The minimum quantity of tokens to receive in exchange for the redeemTokens.
params.deadline: The timestamp for a trade to fail at if not successful.
params.optionToken: The address of the Option contract.
params.path: The token addresses to trade through using their Uniswap V2 pools. Assumes path[0] = redeemToken.
params.to: The address to send the redeemToken proceeds and optionTokens to.

returns._0: bool Whether the transaction was successful or not.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeLiquidityThenCloseOptions(address,.details: Combines Uniswap V2 Router "removeLiquidity" function with Primitive "closeOptions" function.

params.amountAMin: The minimum quantity of optionTokens to receive from removing liquidity.
params.amountBMin: The minimum quantity of quoteTokens to receive from removing liquidity.
params.deadline: The timestamp to expire a pending transaction.
params.liquidity: The quantity of liquidity tokens to pull from msg.sender and burn.
params.optionAddress: The address of the option that will be closed from burned UNI-V2 liquidity shares.
params.to: The address that receives quoteTokens from burned UNI-V2, and underlyingTokens from closed options.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

rollOption(address,address,uint256,addre.details: Closes an option position and opens a new one using the freed underlyingTokens.

params.receiver: The address that receives newly minted option and redeem tokens.
params.rollQuantity: The quantity of underlyingTokens to receive from closed options then use to mint new options.

params.amountAMin: The minimum quantity of optionTokens to receive from removing liquidity.
params.amountBMin: The minimum quantity of quoteTokens to receive from removing liquidity.
params.deadline: The timestamp to expire a pending transaction.
params.liquidity: The quantity of UNI-V2 shares to roll from the first Uniswap pool.
params.rollFromOption: The optionToken address to close a UNI-V2 position.
params.rollToOption: The optionToken address to open a UNI-V2 position.
params.to: The address that receives the UNI-V2 shares that have been rolled.

setFactory(address).details: Sets the Uniswap V2 Factory address to use.

setQuoteToken(address).details: Sets the designated stablecoin to use (paired token in Uniswap pools).

setRegistry(address).details: Sets the Primitive V1 Registry address to use.

setRouter(address).details: Sets the Uniswap V2 Router address to use.

setTrader(address).details: Sets the Primitive V1 Trader address to use.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

addLiquidityWithUnderlying(address,uint2.notice: Pulls underlying tokens from msg.sender and pushes UNI-V2 liquidity tokens to the "to" address. underlyingToken -> optionToken -> UNI-V2.

flashloanMintShortOptionsThenSwap(addres.notice: If the first address in the path is not the redeemToken address, the tx will fail. underlyingToken -> redeemToken -> quoteToken. ShortTokens = redeemTokens

mintOptionsThenSwapToTokens(address,uint.notice: If the first address in the path is not the optionToken address, the tx will fail. underlyingToken -> optionToken -> quoteToken.

mintShortOptionsThenSwapToTokens(address.notice: If the first address in the path is not the redeemToken address, the tx will fail. underlyingToken -> redeemToken -> quoteToken. ShortTokens = redeemTokens

removeLiquidityThenCloseOptions(address,.notice: Pulls UNI-V2 liquidity shares with option<>quote token and redeemToken from msg.sender. Then closes the optionTokens and withdraws underlyingTokens to the "to" address. Sends quoteTokens from the burned UNI-V2 liquidity shares to the "to" address. UNI-V2 -> optionToken -> underlyingToken.

rollOption(address,address,uint256,addre.notice: Pulls option and redeem tokens from msg.sender, then sends minted option + redeems to receiver. rollFromOption -> underlyingToken -> rollToOption.

rollOptionLiquidity(address,address,uint.notice: Rolls UNI-V2 liquidity in an option<>quote pair to a different option<>quote pair. UNI-V2 -> rollFromOption -> underlyingToken -> rollToOption -> UNI-V2.
